#include<string.h>
#include<math.h>
#define ll long long

#ifndef ONLINE_JUDGE
#define gc getchar
#define pc putchar
#else
#define gc getchar_unlocked
#define pc putchar_unlocked
#endif

int read_int() {
    char c = gc();
    while(c < '0' || c > '9') c = gc();
    int ret = 0;
    while(c >= '0' && c <= '9') {
        ret = 10 * ret + c - 48;
        c = gc();
    }
    return ret;
}

char S[10][4000];
int res[10][4001], max[10];

int main() {

#ifndef ONLINE_JUDGE
    freopen("testcase.in", "r", stdin);
#endif

    int i, j, c, r, t, a, b, k = 0;

    for(i=1;i<=9;i++) { res[i][0] = 1; max[i] = 0; S[i][0] = '1'; S[i][1] = 0; }

    t = read_int();
    while(t--) {
        a = read_int();
        b = read_int();
        for(i=max[a]+1;i<=b;i++) {
            c = 0;
            for(j=0;S[a][j];j++) {
                r = a*(S[a][j]-'0')+c;
                c = r/10;
                S[a][j] = (r%10)+'0';
            }
            if (c) S[a][j++] = c+'0';
            S[a][j] = 0;
            for(j=0,res[a][i]=0;S[a][j];j++) res[a][i]+=S[a][j]-'0';
        }
        max[a] = b;
        printf("Case %d: %d\n", ++k, res[a][b]);
    }

    return 0;
}
